Description: Fragment of handle to sharpish turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine beige-buff; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Name Armosilas. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 138, 3. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, KF126/1000126.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0687)
